Body colour off-white or grey in alcohol (Fig. 4
A-D
); papillae minute, especially behind segment 7 and near shield on dorsal side, or smooth, apparently without papillae. Anterior region often swollen and bulbous, sometimes wider than posterior region, with a constriction at septum between segments 7 and 8 (Fig. 4D). Neotype 14.6 mm long (paraneotypes 11.9-17.0 mm long), 12 mm wide, with about 30 segments.

First three chaetigers with more than 12-14 hooks, bronze with subdistal dark band (Fig. 4E). Genital papillae between segments 7-8 (Fig. 4
B-D
). Pre-shield region with 7 segments, sometimes bearing small fascicles of fine capillary chaetae.
